I wrote a quick check on `master` to verify that ancestors passed into CMPA are indeed always a subset of what is returned at the end of CMPA. At least as far as the scenarios covered in the unit and functional tests, that seems to be the case, since with this patch all tests complete without throwing.

<details>
<summary>git diff on master (5974c49f9)</summary>

```diff
diff --git a/src/txmempool.cpp b/src/txmempool.cpp
index 84ed2e9ef..e024ebe81 100644
--- a/src/txmempool.cpp
+++ b/src/txmempool.cpp
@@ -190,6 +190,8 @@ bool CTxMemPool::CalculateAncestorsAndCheckLimits(size_t entry_size,
                                                   const Limits& limits,
                                                   std::string &errString) const
 {
+    setEntries incoming_ancestors{setAncestors.begin(), setAncestors.end()};
+    setAncestors.clear();
     size_t totalSizeWithAncestors = entry_size;
 
     while (!staged_ancestors.empty()) {
@@ -226,6 +228,9 @@ bool CTxMemPool::CalculateAncestorsAndCheckLimits(size_t entry_size,
         }
     }
 
+    for (auto& ancestor : incoming_ancestors){
+        if (setAncestors.find(ancestor) == setAncestors.end()) throw std::runtime_error("incoming ancestor not found");
+    }
     return true;
 }
 ```
</details>

